BMW M3 E30 195hk
cars.description:
Nu har vi fått in ett fint exemplar av den klassiska Bmw M3 E30. Denna bil levererades ny 4 April 1990 i Toulouse Frankrike, första ägaren fick motorn utbytt 1992 (kvitto finns). Bilen såldes sedan samma år av samma BMW återförsäljare i Toulouse, denna ägaren behöll bilen till 2010 och sålde den sedan till sista ägaren som haft bilen fram to m 2024.
Extremt väldokumenterad bil som fått mycket kärlek av sina tidigare ägare, Hel och fräsch invändigt och utvändigt, Nya däck 2023. Hartge tidsenliga fälgar, Vi hjälper er med förmånlig finansiering och självklart tar vi er bil i inbyte. Kontakta oss gärna för mer information.

Avaible for Export
Diamond Black (Diamant Schwarz) exterior - Black leather interior
First MEC : 18/04/1990

History: This M3 E30 was delivered new to Toulouse on April 4, as attested by the car´s original logbook. In 1992, the original engine was replaced by an engine from the same series with the same mileage (on invoice). The car was then sold to its second owner by the BMW dealership in Toulouse. The second owner kept the car until 2010, when he sold it to the current owner. On receipt, the owner sends the car to Delage for extensive servicing and preparation (running gear, the car has been serviced every year.

Condition:
General: This M3 is in a very good condition. A rare car, its history is clear and well known.

Exterior: The bodywork is in excellent condition. The black "Diamond" paint is very well preserved. Plastics, glazing and headlights look like new. The carbon spoiler and front blade are in very good condition. The Hartge rims are flawless.

Interior: The interior is in superb condition. The original leather seats have stood the test of time. The same is true of the carpets, floor mats and headliner. All interior components are functional (Blaupunkt radio, etc.).

Mechanical: The few modifications made by Delage concern the running gear (Bilstein + short springs), brakes group N. an anti-bumping bar. a Supersprint stainless steel exhaust system. The engine runs and starts normally both hot and cold. Undercarriage settings are precise, and roadholding is very pleasant.

Invoice file
Stamped maintenance booklet
Stamped warranty booklet
Owner´s manual
Technical inspection
Certificate of administrative status
Duplicate keys
